Aide mémoire pour utilisation de Git / Github

Pour importer un repo à partir de Github

Se positionner dans le répertoire ou l'on souhaite installer le repo
> cd <rep_cible>
> git clone https://github/pperisseau/<nom_projet>

# pour connaitre le status des changements 
> git status

# If you add new files in repo, you need to let Git know that they need to be track
> git add .     (add all new files)
> git add -u    (update tracking for files that changed names or were deleted)
> git add -A    (does both of the previous)

you should do this before commiting

You have change you want to commit to be saved as n intermediate version

> git commit -m "message of desription"
this action only updates the local repo, not Github

# when you want to push your local repo to Github
> git push

# to create a new branch
> git checkout -b <branchname>

# to check what branch you are on type :
> git branch

# to switch to another branch type
> git checkout <branchname>

# to delete a branch on a local repo
> git branch -d the_local_branch


aide en ligne :
https://help.github.com/
https://git-scm.com/doc